text.paragraph:
The maximum recommended single dose is 40 mg. 


 In controlled clinical trials, single doses of 20 mg and 40 mg were effective for the acute treatment of migraine in adults. A greater proportion of patients had a response following a 40 mg dose than following a 20 mg dose [see Clinical Studies (14

                     )].

list.item:
Recent use (i.e., within at least 72 hours) of the following potent CYP3A4 inhibitors: ketoconazole, itraconazole, nefazodone, troleandomycin, clarithromycin, ritonavir, or nelfinavir [see Drug Interactions (7.2

                        ) and Clinical Pharmacology (12.3

                        )].

Hypersensitivity reactions [see Contraindications (4

                        ) and Warnings and Precautions (5.9

                        )]
